The paper deals with link prediction in networks, which is a common problem in network science and can be applied to various fields such as social networks, biological networks, and transportation networks. The paper specifically focuses on predicting triangles (cliques of three nodes) in networks, which are important structures in social networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
